If your using windows, try my ReadNES2. It will do this easier if you don't have a text editor handy, and if there's a CHR-ROM, It will save you loads of time.<br /><br /><br />Edit the batch file and put the .nes's ROM name in there instead. It will make 2 .BIN files for you to burn to a EPROM/ROM. Even though the CHR=0, It still makes a file I think....thats something that will maybe be fixed if I ever change it again.<br /><br /><br />Anyway, here's the link, good luck! <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /><br /><br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://aaronrls01.webs.com/Etc/ReadNES2.zip">http://aaronrls01.webs.com/Etc/ReadNES2.zip</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4311">3gengames</a> — Wed Sep 15, 2010 9:34 pm</p><hr />
