<title type="html"><![CDATA[Can't split .nes file?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6955&amp;p=67554#p67554"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">Aituon wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />So then what eprom would I use? 27C1001?<br /></div><br />That will do. Keep in mind that the size of these chips are usually measured in kilo<strong>bits</strong>. To convert kilo<strong>bits</strong> to kilo<strong>bytes</strong> you have to divide the number by 8.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br />How would I get rid of the .nes to get the prg bin file?<br /></div><br />ROMs that don't have CHR (like is the case with Castlevania) are just made of a 16-byte header followed by the PRG. The header is always 16 bytes, so you can just open the ROM in an hex editor and delete the first 16 bytes. Save it as a new file and check the size: Castlevania should be exactly 131072 bytes (128KBytes).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Wed Sep 15, 2010 9:02 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
