<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6955&amp;p=67545#p67545"><![CDATA[
27C512 is 64kB (512 kilobits), Castlevania is twice that size.  It's just one ROM so there's nothing to split other than the header, you could use a hex editor to remove the first 16 bytes.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Wed Sep 15, 2010 5:51 pm</p><hr />
